{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0e4a2292-4b82-44a2-8fc7-c70eedcaec8b","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files are compiled top-to-bottom as listed in the `.fsproj`. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but it's listed *before* it. Let me fix the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_NGsxwRK54osIeK7dy1Wchs","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-29d20becf79a46d0b065dfc45ed6e80f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-29d20becf79a46d0b065dfc45ed6e80f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"2ef63843-454b-4771-98bb-cc6c63e1ad05","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files must be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj` file. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), but in the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`. This means the compiler will try to compile `Services.fs` first, but it won't find the `BrokenOrder.Domain` module yet.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"F03D:149EED:45E996F:4D90941:69F9B07C"},"id":"d7f8aa2e-a86f-4451-8213-94afd85b3d4b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:32.454Z","parentId":"bdfdacde-4f50-4f77-89a9-16e74eb2a003"}
